
[Cone]
A 3-dimensional figure with parallel and congruent bases.

[Lateral Area of a Cone]
The lateral surface area of a right circular cone follows the formula L = πrl,
where (lowercase) l is the cone's slant height and r is the radius of the base.
.
.  The surface area of a cone can be written like any other surface area -
.  the sum of its base's area and its lateral area. Using the lateral area
.  of a cone formula and the area of a circle formula (since a circular cone's
.  base is, of course, a circle), we can write the surface area of a cone as
.  such:
.
.    S = πrl + πr^2, where S is the surface area of the cone, r is the radius
.                    of the cone's base circle, and l is the slant height of
.                    the cone.

