What is the surface area of a cone with a diameter of 10 centimeters and a
slant height of 12 centimeters? Round your answer to the nearest whole number.
(Use 3.14 as an approximation for pi.)

Radius..............
r = d/2
r = 10/2
r = 5

Lateral area........
L = πrl
L = π(5)(12)
L = 60π
L = 188.4

Base area...........
B = πr^2
B = π(5^2)
B = 25π
B = 78.5

Total surface area..
S = L + B
S = 188.4 + 78.5
S = 266.9

