The surface area of a cone is 40.5π square feet and its radius is 3 feet.
What is the slant height of the cone?

Base area.......
B = πr^2
B = π(3^2)
B = 9π

Lateral area....
S = L + B
40.5π = L + 9π
L = 40.5π - 9π
L = 31.5π

Slant height....
L = πrl
31.5π = 3π(l)
31.5 = 3(l)
10.5 = l

